&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;A-TEK is seeking a motivated AV Engineer 1 to support our Federal Customer in Montgomery, MD. AV Engineer 1 assists with the installation, commissioning, troubleshooting, and maintenance of professional audio-visual systems. Working under the guidance of senior engineers, this role supports conference rooms, auditoriums, digital signage, video conferencing systems, and live event environments.&lt;strong&gt; Ability to obtain and retain a public trust level clearance is required for consideration. This is a hybrid position based in Rockville, MD. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities and Duties: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in installing AV equipment such as displays, projectors, speakers, microphones, cameras, and control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and test video conferencing platforms (Microsoft Teams Rooms, Zoom Rooms, Cisco Webex).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run, terminate, and label AV cabling (HDMI, CAT6, audio cables).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot hardware, software, and connectivity issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond and track service request tickets using ServiceNow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform preventive maintenance and system upgrades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support live meetings, presentations, and special events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare documentation, wiring diagrams, and installation reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with senior engineers during system integration and commissioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow company safety standards and installation best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide basic user training and technical support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s or bachelor’s degree in Audio Engineering, Electronics, Information Technology, Computer Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0–2 years of AV or IT support experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audio systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Video displays and projectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AV signal flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Networking fundamentals (TCP/IP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Teams or Zoom&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to use hand and power tools safely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication and teamwork skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel to customer sites if required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
